Installing PyServ:
  1. login into root
  2. run "setup.py"
  3. login into a normal user
  4. open "pyserv.conf" and change values
  5. create mysql database
  6. insert sql/base/struct.sql into the database
  7. run "pyserv.py" as normal user or "start" in a screen

Updating PyServ:
  1. insert the sqls in sql/updates into the mysql database
  2. delete this sqls to be shure that you didnt insert the sqls at next update
  3. run "pyserv.py" as normal user or "start" in a screen

Converting your Database from SQLite3 to MySQL:

  1. move your data.db into the tools directory
  2. run "sqlite3 data.db .dump | python convert.py > data.sql"
  3. create a database in mysql
  4. insert the data.sql into your mysql database
  5. if there is an error, remove the first line from data.sql an try again
